### Section 4: BvP-Favorable — Home Runs
Top 25 **filtered to batters with BvP HR > 0 against tonight's pitcher**, then **sorted by BvP HR count descending** (most career HRs vs this pitcher first). Ties broken by **raw `p_hr`** descending. Same table columns as Section 1 plus BvP HR count column. If fewer than 25 qualify, show all that do.

### Section 5: BvP-Favorable — Hits
Top 25 **filtered to batters with BvP BA ≥ .250 and PA ≥ 5 against tonight's pitcher**, then **sorted by BvP hits descending** (most career hits vs this pitcher first). Ties broken by **raw `p_hit`** descending. Same table columns as Section 2 plus BvP hits column. If fewer than 25 qualify, show all that do.

### Section 6: BvP-Favorable — XBH
Top 25 **filtered to batters with BvP XBH > 0 against tonight's pitcher**, then **sorted by BvP XBH count descending** (most career XBH vs this pitcher first). Ties broken by **raw `p_xbh`** descending. Same table columns as Section 3 plus BvP XBH count column. If fewer than 25 qualify, show all that do.

### Section 7: Top 10 HR Full Analysis
For each of the top 10 batters by **raw `p_hr`** (after posterior blend), produce the **full gold-standard HR description** as defined in `homerun-analysis.mdc`. Every single one of the 10 must include ALL of:

1. **Header Block** — Title, Model line (Raw/Adj/Conf/Grade), 3-PA probability line with formula, Confidence factors line (all 6 factors)
2. **Career Power Profile** — HRs, PAs, HR rate vs 3.1% league with multiplier and editorial, peak season, EV mean/max vs ~104 league, LA mean with shape comment, HR by pitch type (top 5-6 with count AND BA), multi-sentence narrative connecting to pitcher's arsenal with "That's the math:", one-sentence summary
3. **The [Pitcher]-Specific HR Case** — BvP line with editorial framing, HR table (Date/Pitch/Velo/EV/LA) if exists, narrative on contact quality + arsenal connection, BvP K rate with editorial, what-happens-when-he-connects narrative
4. **[Pitcher]'s HR Vulnerability** — Career HR allowed/PA/rate vs league with editorial, HR by pitch type, fastball velo/usage with editorial, 2026 stats (ERA/WHIP/BB9/IP/HR) with strong editorial on current form, handedness splits with rate, K%/BB% with HR-variance context
5. **Where [Batter] Ranks Tonight** — Rank of total by raw P(HR) with percentile, rank within team
6. **The Verdict on the HR Bet** — Three bold-labeled paragraphs: **For** (multi-sentence), **Against** (multi-sentence, honest), **Net** (raw P per PA → 3-PA formula → 1-in-X odds → rank → positioning statement with conditional)

**Do NOT shorten these. Each write-up should be roughly the same length as the Brandon Lowe canonical example (~400-500 words).**

### Section 8: Top 10 Hit Full Analysis
For each of the top 10 batters by **raw `p_hit`** (after posterior blend), produce the **full gold-standard Hit description** as defined in `hit-analysis.mdc`. Every single one of the 10 must include ALL of:

1. **Header Block** — Title, Model line (Raw/Adj/Conf/Grade), 3-PA probability line with formula, Confidence factors line (all 6 factors)
2. **Career Contact Profile** — Hits, PAs, BA vs .243 league with editorial, K rate vs ~22% league, doubles/HR for XBH context, EV on hits mean, hits by pitch type (top 5-6 with count AND BA), pitch-group splits (BA/EV/whiff vs fastball/breaking/offspeed), multi-sentence narrative connecting to pitcher's arsenal, one-sentence contact summary
3. **The [Pitcher]-Specific Hit Case** — BvP line with editorial framing (Strong/Struggled/No BvP/Tiny sample), BvP K rate with editorial, narrative connecting BvP to arsenal and pitch-type matchup logic
4. **[Pitcher]'s Hit Vulnerability** — BA allowed with hit count/AB vs league, K rate and BB rate with context, arsenal breakdown (fastball %/velo, breaking %, offspeed %), BA by batter handedness with editorial, 2026 stats with strong editorial on current form
5. **Where [Batter] Ranks Tonight** — Rank of total by raw P(Hit) with percentile, rank within team
6. **The Verdict on the Hit Bet** — Three bold-labeled paragraphs: **For** (multi-sentence), **Against** (multi-sentence, honest), **Net** (raw P per PA → 3-PA formula → 1-in-X odds → rank → positioning statement with conditional)

**Do NOT shorten these. Each write-up should be roughly the same length as the HR canonical example (~400-500 words).**

